1. e4 c5 2. c4
{ This is a move that aims to confuse Black and steer the game either into an English Opening - you can argue this arose after 1.c4 c5 2.e4 - or into a Maroczy bind if White manages to push d4. Unless Black plays the Accelerated Fianchetto and is not against a transposition to the Maroczy, or he plays the Taimanov and can go ...e6 and ...Nc6 here, allowing d4, there isn't much leeway to avoid an unfavourable transposition, so be careful with the following variation. }
2... Nc6 3. Ne2 Nf6 4. Nbc3 e6
{ Black will push ...d5 in order to prevent White's plan of d4. } 5. d4 d5 6.
cxd5 exd5 { After } 7. e5 { Black has } 7... Ng4
{ and White's centre collapses after } 8. h3 cxd4 *

