1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ The Wing Gambit isn't very serious and Black's best reaction is to play in the centre after taking the pawn. }
2... cxb4 3. a3 d5
{ Following the rules - play in the centre is the best antidote to wing provocations. }
4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nf3 e5 { After } 6. Bb2 Nc6 7. axb4 Bxb4 8. c4 Qd6
{ Black has excellent play, as the 'combination' } 9. Nxe5
{ doesn't work in more than one way. Here's the simplest: } 9... Nxe5 10. Qe2
f6 11. f4 Bg4 12. fxe5 Bxe2 13. exd6 Bxf1 14. Kxf1 Bxd6
{ with a clear pawn up in the endgame. } *

