1. e4 c5 2. Na3
{ This is not as silly as it appears. The move Na3 is typical for the Alapin Sicilian so White tries to steer the game towards those lines while at the same time keeping Rossolimo ideas like Bb5 and g3, Bg2 plans at his disposal. }
2... d5 { Giving check by } 3. Bb5+ { is met by } 3... Nc6
{ and White cannot go along the positional lines after } 4. Bxc6+ bxc6 5. d3
{ because after } 5... e5
{ Black's full centre, bishop pair and the stranded knight on a3 all outweigh the doubled c-pawns. }
