{ Now Black continues with the usual development. } 9. d4
{ Insisting on the immediate d4. } 9... cxd4 10. Nxd4 O-O
{ The point of Black's play is seen after } 11. b3 d5
{ as it takes advantage of the pin on the c-file in view of the undefended knight on c3. Then }
12. e5 Ne8 { isn't dangerous and after } 13. Rd1 dxc4 14. bxc4 Qa5
{ Black can look forward to playing against the weak c4-pawn. } *

