1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. Bb5+
{ The Moscow Variation is practically as equally popular as the main lines of the open Sicilian. It conveniently allows White to avoid the forcing lines of the open Sicilians while at the same time giving him a playable middlegame position. }
