6. Qe2
{ The hedgehog plan with a queen on e2 is considered the most promising for White. }
6... e6 { Continuing with the usual development. } 7. c3
{ Building a full centre with the queen on e2 is met in the same manner as with the rook on e1 instead. }
7... Be7 8. d4 O-O
{ Just as in the line with 6 Re1 Black ignores White's centre. } 9. e5
{ The difference with the 6 Re1 line is that here the rook can be placed more actively on the d-file, so White tries to open the game. In case of other moves Black can follow the same recipe by taking on d4 and playing ...Rc8, ... Nb6 etc. }
9... Ne8 { Black's reaction is the same. The only difference is that after }
10. Rd1 cxd4 11. cxd4 { Now instead of taking on e5 Black plays } 11... Nc7
{ Black sensibly refrains from opening the d-file while at the same time employing the same idea to put a knight on d5. White cannot stop this as }
12. Nc3 { Is met by } 12... Nb6
{ And on the next move the knight will land on d5. } *

